  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 220°C/ 200°C (fan)/ gas 7</p><p>Boil a kettle</p><p>Chop the <strong>waxy potatoes</strong> in half</p><p>Add the <strong>halved potatoes</strong> to a pot of plenty of <strong>boiled water</strong> with a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and bring to the boil over a high heat</p><p>Once boiling, cook for 12-15 min or until fork-tender, then drain and return to the pot to steam dry</p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1610020015602-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1610020015602-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1610020015602-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1610020015602-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1610020015602-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) over a medium-high heat</p><p>Once hot, add the<strong> lean beef mince</strong> and cook for 4-5 min or until browned all over, breaking it up with a wooden spoon as you go</p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1610020033455-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1610020033455-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1610020033455-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1610020033455-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1610020033455-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Whilst the lean beef mince is cooking, peel and finely chop the <strong>brown</strong> <strong>onion<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span></strong></p><p>Top, tail, peel and dice the <strong>carrot<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span></strong></p><p>Once the beef has<strong> </strong>browned, add the <strong>chopped onion</strong> and <strong>diced</strong> <strong>carrot </strong>to the pan with a generous pinch of<strong> salt</strong> and cook for a further 4-5 min or until softened</p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1610020043988-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
